Mario Kart: Double Dash!! is a racing game developed by Nintendo Entertainment Analysis and Development and published by Nintendo for the Nintendo GameCube.
Nintendo Power gave the game a perfect score, and stated that the graphics were of "3-D perfection" and that the controls and game mechanics "rival those of any GCN racing game." Double Dash!! also received a perfect score from GamePro, who commented that the gameplay remains "fast and furious".
GameSpy called Double Dash!! a "great- looking, great-playing game that most gamers will instantly warm to." Eurogamer declared that the game was one of the "finest pieces of electronic entertainment ever developed." The game received the "Multiplayer Game" award from ITV's Game Stars in 2004.
